teams.name: Becky's Hugs
teams.loan_because: Becky was unfailingly generous during her short life (2001-2010).  She loved freely and without limit, and never met anyone she considered to be a stranger.  She was always ready with a hug for anyone who needed one, even when they didn't know it yet.  Loaning Becky's memory keeps her love alive, spreading her love around the world!
teams.description:
We are a group of people who have been inspired by the love of a young lady named Becky, who was tragically killed 30 August 2010 at the age of 9½.  She loved unconditionally, and was always ready with a hug, even for complete strangers.  The living memorial of sharing hugs began immediately after her death, when her mother told her classmates to hug each other every day in her memory.  This team keeps Becky's love alive by sharing her hugs in the form of loans around the world.

To learn more about Becky and the impact of her short life, visit BeckysHugs.com, which will point you to the Becky's Hugs page on Facebook.  Look at the photos and videos to get a better idea about who Becky was, and check out the timeline to see the ways in which people have celebrated her memory and love.

Hugs to you!

teams.description:
In our team, we have a vision to change lives in novel ways. Our team's origin began with a Kiva Card (gift certificate) whose recipient founded this team. Inspired by Kiva Fellow, Jessica Heinzelman's talk, our founder dreamed to take us on a cruise, beyond the realm of lending targets and team statistics. Frequent & occasional lenders are free to choose who to lend to, how much and when in an amiable team ambience nurtured by Kiva Fellows, Kiva Editor & Translators, artists, writers, entrepreneurs, workers, retired people, families, parent + kid(s), students, teachers, and professionals. Our diversity & portfolio enable our discovery of social values inherent in the Kiva micro-lending ecosystem whose issues we debate objectively. Experienced members are gratified to enhance our grasp of nuances in lending. We wish to work with volunteers in the team, Kiva Friends, http://kivafriends.org and our supporters to engage in activities that promote Kiva. Our journey to strengthen and grow the Kiva ecosystem has room for more. JOIN NOW, and check out our team, to convince yourself that it can be your team too.

LINKS TO SEE ALSO:
1. Kiva Updates:http://www.kiva.org/updates/kiva 
2. KF Blogs:http://www.kiva.org/updates/fellows

teams.name: Sirel Mouchantaf
teams.loan_because:
Sirel Mouchantaf is an engineering professional working in Fredericksburg, VA with over twenty years of experience in heavy civil and rail projects. He graduated with a Bachelor’s Degree in Civil Engineering and a Master’s Degree in Engineering Management (MSEM) from Syracuse University. The MSEM program helps working engineers and scientists become better managers as well as  become prepared for increased responsibilities in management. The degree program provided Sirel with knowledge in management theory and practices, statistics, quality control, finance, economics, information/data management, and legal issues. With this specialized knowledge and training, Sirel has lead and developed the engineering and construction department at the Virginia Railway Express (VRE) for the past ten years.

While working for VRE, Sirel quickly rose through the ranks due to his ability to execute projects on time and under budget. His direct construction experience provides the added value of ensuring project constructability with minimal potential for contractor claims. Prior to joining the VRE, Sirel has worked in both the private and public sector leading and participating in major capital projects. Sirel is a licensed Professional Engineer in multiple states and a certified construction manager. Regulation and licensing in engineering is performed by the individual states and is only valid in the state it is granted. This process was created to protect the general public and ensure that the engineer is prepared to provide services.

In his spare time, Sirel enjoys spending time with his family and working on home improvement projects. Sirel is also a huge soccer fan and continues to be active in the sport with multiple leagues in the DC, Virginia and Maryland areas.

teams.name: Mark Bronner Diamonds
teams.loan_because:
Mark Bronner is a respected diamond dealer in the greater New York area. He has been in the diamond business in the tri-state area for nearly two decades.

Originally, Mark Bronner hails from the Philadelphia suburb of Downingtown, Pennsylvania. He was one of five children. Mark Bronner’s father was an economics professor at Penn and his mother worked at St. Joseph’s Hospital.

Growing up, the boys knew the value of hard work. Starting at the age of 15, each of the four Bronner boys worked construction at Daniel J. Keating for 40 hours a week in the summers.

Bronner enrolled at Malvern Prep, like his three older brothers. While his brothers played hockey and tennis, Bronner was drawn to football and lacrosse. Football came easy to Bronner, and he started on the Malvern prep team as a sophomore safety. Lacrosse proved more difficult, and Bronner considered quitting the Friars lacrosse team as a sophomore. However, in his final and senior campaign, Mark Bronner became a starter at long stick midfield and earned a partial scholarship to the University of Delaware.

While at the University of Delaware, Mark Bronner initially majored in Biology. He intended to be medical doctor. However, while in school, his father, James Bronner, left Penn to move into the private sector. Mark Bronner became drawn to Business, and graduated with a Bachelors of Science.

Following college, Bronner got hired at his old company, Keating Construction. In a supply-chain management role, Mark Bronner helped the company expand its footprint significantly and improved efficiency. By the time he was thirty, Bronner moved into a management role. He aided in the acquisition of some smaller construction firms in his managerial position.

Bronner noticed his own ability to recognize sound business, and began a career in personal investing. He started by investing in small chain restaurants in the Philadelphia suburbs. Bronner diversified by getting into commodities, specifically energy. However, when a former teammate from the Delaware Blue Hen lacrosse team came to him with an opportunity with diamonds, Bronner could not pass it up

teams.name: John C. Flaherty
teams.loan_because:
John C. Flaherty was mostly raised in the Midwest in a town called Galesburg, Illinois.  He relocated with his family to Las Vegas, Nevada when he was young. Flaherty attended the University of Nevada-Las Vegas, graduating with a Bachelors of Science in Business Administration with an emphasis in Marketing.

Shortly after finishing college, John C. Flaherty was hired on as an agent with Prudential Life Insurance Company. There, Flaherty quickly learned about the insurance industry and saw success in sales.  After spending many years in Las Vegas, Flaherty moved to the Seattle, Washington area where he worked in regional sales for Metlife.  Flaherty oversaw the Western Division for the insurance company.

In 2005, Flaherty was given an opportunity to branch out and he opened his own financial agency.  He operates John C. Flaherty Inc., located in Puyallup, Washington.

Professional

Flaherty tailors financial tools for executives and professionals, owners of closely held businesses and other clients requiring expert assistance with life insurance, business insurance, disability insurance and other financial products.

John Flaherty brings a wealth of experience in different financial fields. He has earned a reputation for providing skilled and practical guidance as a financial consultant.

Flaherty’s areas of expertise include implementing protection of family and business assets, and tax recapture strategies. John C. Flaherty Inc. emphasizes

maximizing access to your money and maximizing protection and risk management. He utilizes an economic model to measure, verify, and implement strategic financial decisions.

Flaherty is also an active member of Toastmasters International. As the name suggests, Toastmasters is an organization that helps individuals become better public speakers. Long active in training of other financial professionals, John C. Flaherty has spoken throughout the United States on a variety of issues pertaining to Life & Disability Insurance and how to sell it.

John C. Flaherty presently resides in Puyallup, Washington with his family.
